info.senderName: NWS Key West (Key West - The Florida Keys)
info.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued October 09 at 10:20PM EDT until October 10 at 11:00AM EDT by NWS Key West
info.description: ...COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT... * WHAT...Saltwater flooding. * WHERE...Bayside communities of the Upper Florida Keys. * WHEN...Until 11 AM EDT Tuesday. * IMPACTS...Saltwater flooding of low elevation streets and lots is expected. Some storm drains will overflow, and some seawalls and docks will be overtopped. Boaters can expect less clearance under fixed bridges. Motorists should remember that persistent puddles around the times of high tide are almost certain to contain a mix of saltwater.
info.instruction: If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone property.
